20:59.550 --> 21:01.723
RADIO CHORUS [SINGING]:
W-S-K-I-D

21:01.886 --> 21:03.980
Skid Row radio.

21:04.138 --> 21:07.392
MAN [ON RADIO]: You're listening
to radio station WSKID, home of the hits.

21:07.558 --> 21:10.937
In just a few minutes we'll bring you
Wink Wilkinson 's Weird World...

21:11.103 --> 21:14.607
the show that talks to wonderful people
who bring in their weird things.

21:14.774 --> 21:17.072
But first, the weather.

21:17.234 --> 21:18.656
Thank you very much, Tom.

21:18.819 --> 21:22.289
The weather today will be partly cloudy
with a chance of rain. Sorry about that.

21:22.448 --> 21:24.871
The high temperature
will be in the low 50s tonight...

21:25.034 --> 21:26.536
so get out those electric blankets.

21:26.702 --> 21:28.875
Tomorrow we'll start off
with morning haze...

21:29.038 --> 21:31.882
- Excuse me. I was told to come...
- Yeah, you're next.

21:32.041 --> 21:34.089
MAN:
High tomorrow should be in the low 70s...

21:34.251 --> 21:35.878
<i>with the low in the high 60s.</i>

21:36.045 --> 21:38.889
In the suburbs, the sun should be out
through most of the day...

21:39.048 --> 21:41.050
except for some cloudy patches
in the evening...

21:41.217 --> 21:43.219
but I don't think it'll
affect your barbecue.

21:43.385 --> 21:46.855
The barometer reading should be 21.6.
The wind will be about...

21:47.014 --> 21:49.062
uh, I'd say 12 miles per hour...

21:49.225 --> 21:51.444
so watch it out there on those boats.

21:51.602 --> 21:55.323
The sun will be rising tomorrow
at about 7:17 a. m...

21:55.481 --> 21:59.577
and it should be setting around
6:29 p.m., but check me if I'm wrong.

21:59.735 --> 22:01.658
A cold front is moving in
from the south-west.

22:01.821 --> 22:03.414
But it should brighten up by noon.

22:03.572 --> 22:06.576
The weekend should be mild.
For you average-mean-temperature fans...

22:06.742 --> 22:10.497
the average mean temperature
for the season is 69 degrees, not too bad.

22:10.663 --> 22:12.586
Thank you, and back to you.

22:12.748 --> 22:13.795
[TWOEY GRUNTS]

22:13.958 --> 22:16.632
MAN:
You're listening to radio station WSKID.

22:16.794 --> 22:17.920
[RADIO JINGLE PLAYING]

22:18.087 --> 22:21.762
And now, Wink Wilkinson's Weird World,
with your host, Wink Wilkinson.

22:21.924 --> 22:24.143
[HORN HONKING & BELL RINGING]

22:24.301 --> 22:27.145
Hi everybody! It's Weird Wink Wilkinson,
laughing and scratching at you.

22:27.304 --> 22:28.430
How's everybody doing today?

22:28.597 --> 22:30.440
I got a bit of a stiff neck.
Let me fix this up.

22:30.599 --> 22:31.646
[CLACKING]

22:31.809 --> 22:34.358
Ooh, that feels a lot better!
I got a great show for you today...

22:34.520 --> 22:37.194
with some wonderful weird stuff!

22:37.398 --> 22:39.571
What are you doing here?

22:39.733 --> 22:41.360
What? You... Please, lady, no!

22:41.527 --> 22:43.825
Put your clothes back on!
You can't do this to me!

22:43.988 --> 22:45.456
What if your husband were to walk in?

22:45.614 --> 22:47.332
[IN LOW VOICE]
I'm here. I love your show...

22:47.491 --> 22:49.459
but I've got to kill you
with this machine gun.

22:49.618 --> 22:51.666
[MIMICS MACHINE GUN FIRING]

22:52.288 --> 22:53.540
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Oh, you got me!

22:53.706 --> 22:55.708
[MOANING]

22:55.875 --> 22:59.220
I feel... I feel so very weird!

22:59.378 --> 23:00.675
[LAUGHING]

23:00.838 --> 23:02.260
Our first guest is a young man...

23:02.423 --> 23:05.893
you probably read about in the
newspapers, by the name of, um...

23:06.051 --> 23:08.053
Seymour Krelborn. Is that correct?

23:08.220 --> 23:11.144
Who has discovered a new breed of plant
hitherto unknown on this planet.

23:11.307 --> 23:13.105
Let me play you down
to your seat, Seymour.

23:13.267 --> 23:15.895
[DINGING]

23:16.061 --> 23:17.904
Hello, Seymour!

23:18.272 --> 23:19.774
Um...

23:19.940 --> 23:21.408
Hello, Wink.

23:21.567 --> 23:23.535
I wish you folks at home could see this.

23:23.694 --> 23:27.244
Seymour, where did you get
such a weird plant?

23:30.701 --> 23:35.958
Well, you remember that total eclipse
of the sun about a week ago?

23:36.582 --> 23:39.802
WINK [ON RADIO]: Thus we conclude
our interview with the young botanical...

23:39.960 --> 23:41.553
<i>- Mind if I call you</i> a <i>genius?
- Oh, hoo.</i>

23:41.712 --> 23:42.804
SEYMOUR:
Gosh, no!

23:42.963 --> 23:45.842
WINK: The genius who's discovered
this amazing, unidentified plant.

23:46.008 --> 23:49.387
SEYMOUR: I'd like to remind our listeners
that the Audrey ll is on display...

23:49.553 --> 23:51.601
exclusively at Mushnik's
Skid Row Florists.

23:51.764 --> 23:52.981
- Shh!
- Am I late? Did I miss it?

23:53.140 --> 23:55.268
SEYMOUR: Mushnik's.
WINK: Until next week...

23:55.434 --> 23:57.778
- The address.
WINK: this is Wilkinson saying...

23:57.937 --> 24:00.156
- The address!
SEYMOUR: six days a week...

24:00.314 --> 24:02.612
I said, mention the address!

24:02.775 --> 24:04.277
RADIO CHORUS [SINGING]:
Skid Row radio.

24:04.443 --> 24:07.993
Ugh. Oh, well. It's still good advertising.

24:08.155 --> 24:10.624
Seymour's first radio broadcast.

24:10.783 --> 24:14.458
I wanted to hear it so bad.
I tried to be on time, but...

24:14.620 --> 24:16.543
Don't tell me. You got tied up.

24:16.705 --> 24:19.083
No, just handcuffed a little.

24:21.168 --> 24:23.091
Girl. Hey, girl.

24:23.253 --> 24:25.506
I don't know who this mess is
you been hanging out with...

24:25.673 --> 24:27.300
but he is hazardous to your health.

24:27.466 --> 24:29.764
That's for sure. But I can't leave him.

24:29.927 --> 24:32.021
- Why not?
- Oh, he'd get angry.

24:32.179 --> 24:36.229
And if he does this to me when he likes me,
imagine what he'd do if he ever got mad.

24:36.392 --> 24:39.521
So? Dump the chump.
Get another guy and let him protect you.

24:39.687 --> 24:42.190
How about the little jerk with the glasses?

24:42.356 --> 24:43.528
- Seymour?
- That's him.

24:43.691 --> 24:45.819
Oh, we're just friends.

24:45.985 --> 24:49.535
I don't even deserve
a sweet, considerate...

24:49.697 --> 24:52.496
suddenly successful guy like Seymour.

24:52.658 --> 24:55.081
That poor child
suffers from low self-image.

24:55.244 --> 24:57.463
- You got a point.
- She got a problem.

24:59.331 --> 25:03.586
[SINGING]
I know Seymour's the greatest.

25:04.169 --> 25:09.676
But I'm dating a semi-sadist.

25:09.842 --> 25:14.564
So I got a black eye
And my arm's in a cast.

25:18.183 --> 25:22.313
Still, that Seymour's a cutie.

25:24.231 --> 25:31.240
Well, if not, he's got inner beauty.

25:31.405 --> 25:34.329
And I dream of a place.

25:34.491 --> 25:40.919
Where we could be together at last.

25:43.876 --> 25:48.677
A matchbox of our own.

25:49.006 --> 25:53.933
A fence of real chain link.

25:54.219 --> 25:58.349
A grill out on the patio.

25:58.515 --> 26:02.019
Disposal in the sink.

26:02.186 --> 26:05.816
A washer and a dryer.

26:05.981 --> 26:10.657
And an ironing machine.

26:10.819 --> 26:13.914
In a tract house that we share.

26:14.073 --> 26:17.543
Somewhere that's green.

26:27.169 --> 26:30.844
He rakes and trims the grass.

26:31.006 --> 26:35.102
He loves to mow and weed

26:35.260 --> 26:38.810
I cook like Betty Crocker.

26:38.972 --> 26:42.977
And I look like Donna Reed.

26:43.143 --> 26:47.114
There's plastic on the furniture.

26:47.272 --> 26:50.947
To keep it neat and clean.

26:51.110 --> 26:54.205
In the Pine-Sol scented air.

26:54.363 --> 26:59.790
Somewhere that's green

27:12.965 --> 27:15.434
[CHIRPING]

27:26.353 --> 27:28.151
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

27:30.023 --> 27:32.401
[HUMMING]

27:32.568 --> 27:37.074
Somewhere that's green.

27:37.239 --> 27:40.584
Between our frozen dinner.

27:40.742 --> 27:44.963
And our bed-time: 9:15.

27:45.122 --> 27:48.752
We snuggle watching Lucy.

27:48.917 --> 27:54.845
On our big, enormous
Twelve-inch screen

27:55.007 --> 28:02.016
I'm his December Bride.

28:03.098 --> 28:08.195
He's father, he knows best.

28:08.353 --> 28:12.153
The kids play Howdy Doody.

28:12.316 --> 28:17.197
As the sun sets in the west.

28:17.362 --> 28:20.491
A picture out of.

28:20.657 --> 28:27.666
Better Homes and Gardens Magazine.

28:34.338 --> 28:39.265
Far from Skid Row

28:41.720 --> 28:46.897
I dream we'll go.

28:50.354 --> 28:56.737
Somewhere that's.

28:58.654 --> 29:00.254
Green

29:29.726 --> 29:32.229
[CHORUS HUMMING]

29:39.695 --> 29:41.789
[SINGING]
Poor Seymour pushed a broom.

29:41.947 --> 29:44.496
Nothing in his news but gloom and doom.

29:44.658 --> 29:47.252
Then he lit a fuse and give him room.

29:47.411 --> 29:50.460
He started an explosion
Holy cow.

29:50.622 --> 29:52.716
That thing went bang, kaboom.

29:52.874 --> 29:56.174
And he's havin' some fun now
Now.

29:56.336 --> 29:58.259
Some fun now Hot damn.

29:58.422 --> 30:00.971
Ain't he havin' some fun now
Yes, ma'am.

30:01.133 --> 30:03.761
He's a havin' some fun now
Oh, boy.

30:03.927 --> 30:06.225
Ain't he havin' some fun now

30:06.388 --> 30:08.436
[ALL CHEERING]

30:16.189 --> 30:17.611
All right!

30:21.653 --> 30:24.327
Now! Some fun now
Sho 'nuff.

30:24.489 --> 30:27.083
Ain't he havin' some fun now
Hot stuff.

30:27.242 --> 30:29.836
He's a havin' some fun now
Oh, boy.

30:29.995 --> 30:33.249
Ain't he havin' some fun now
Now.

30:33.415 --> 30:35.838
Some fun now Good God, good God.

30:36.001 --> 30:38.550
He's havin' some fun now
Oh, boy, oh, boy.

30:38.712 --> 30:40.885
Yeah, he's a havin' some fun now
Oh, boy.

30:41.048 --> 30:43.642
Ain't he havin' some fun now.

30:44.343 --> 30:48.769
Some fun now

30:48.930 --> 30:50.932
[CUSTOMERS CHATTERING]

30:55.062 --> 30:57.064
[PHONES RINGING]

30:58.607 --> 31:01.451
Excuse me, excuse me, excuse me!

31:01.610 --> 31:03.328
Hello?

31:03.487 --> 31:05.489
Hello? Hold on.

31:05.655 --> 31:07.828
Uh, yes, yes. Yes, Mrs. Shiva.

31:07.991 --> 31:11.245
Uh, no, Mrs. Shiva. Right away, Mrs. Shiva.

31:11.411 --> 31:14.210
Seymour! WOMAN: I'd just
like to pay for these, please.

31:14.373 --> 31:16.592
MUSHNIK:
Seymour!

31:16.750 --> 31:19.219
Did you send out the order for Mrs. Shiva?

31:20.003 --> 31:21.721
Mrs. Shiva? I forgot!

31:21.880 --> 31:23.553
You forgot?

31:23.799 --> 31:25.096
You forgot!

31:25.258 --> 31:27.511
Do you hear this, God? He forgot!

31:27.677 --> 31:30.647
Are you listening, customers? He forgot!

31:31.223 --> 31:33.396
Audrey, quick! We've got to do
an emergency arrangement.

31:33.558 --> 31:34.980
Birthday? Wedding? Baby?

31:35.143 --> 31:37.020
- Funeral.
- Hand me the lilies.

31:38.397 --> 31:41.367
Mr. Mushnik's real mad at me, Audrey.
I keep forgetting things.

31:41.525 --> 31:44.074
Scissors. You got a lot on your mind.

31:44.236 --> 31:47.866
Mind? What mind? The Shivas are
our most important funereal account.

31:48.031 --> 31:50.705
A big enormous family,
they're dropping off like flies!

31:50.867 --> 31:54.747
Sometimes I think
Mr. Mushnik's too hard on you. Glue.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.165
That's okay.

31:56.331 --> 31:58.504
- After all, I owe him everything.
- Glitter.

31:58.667 --> 32:02.342
He took me out of the Skid Row Home for
Boys when I was just a little tyke...

32:02.504 --> 32:06.680
gave me a warm place to stay,
floors to sweep, toilets to clean...

32:06.842 --> 32:08.719
and every other Sunday off.

32:08.885 --> 32:13.311
You know, I think you ought
to raise your expectations, Seymour.

32:13.473 --> 32:16.602
Now that you're getting successful,
I mean.

32:16.935 --> 32:19.688
It's clear you suffer
from a low self-image.

32:19.855 --> 32:22.358
And it's high time you get it fixed.

32:22.524 --> 32:25.778
Why don't you go out
and do something nice for yourself like...

32:25.944 --> 32:28.072
buy some new clothes?

32:28.238 --> 32:31.162
Oh, I'm a very bad shopper, Audrey.

32:31.324 --> 32:34.203
I don't have good taste like you.

32:34.411 --> 32:35.833
Oh.

32:35.996 --> 32:39.170
Well, I could help you pick things out.

32:39.332 --> 32:42.381
- You could?
- Sure.

32:42.544 --> 32:44.922
You'd go shopping with me?

32:45.088 --> 32:46.761
Sure.

32:46.923 --> 32:51.303
You'd be seen with me in a public place
like a department store?

32:51.470 --> 32:53.143
Sure.

32:54.139 --> 32:55.391
Tonight?

32:55.557 --> 32:57.810
Oh, I can't tonight. I got a date.

32:57.976 --> 32:59.774
Again, this date?

32:59.936 --> 33:01.062
Some date.

33:01.229 --> 33:03.732
A date gives you a corsage,
not a multiple fracture.

33:03.899 --> 33:07.028
I'm telling you, Audrey,
he's not a good, clean kind of boy.

33:07.194 --> 33:08.411
He's a professional.

33:08.570 --> 33:10.823
What kind of a professional
drives a motorcycle...

33:10.989 --> 33:12.582
and wears a black leather jacket?

33:19.581 --> 33:22.676
[SINGING]
When I was younger, just a bad little kid.

33:22.834 --> 33:25.883
My momma noticed funny things I did.

33:26.046 --> 33:29.141
Like shootin' puppies with a BB gun

33:29.299 --> 33:32.303
I 'd poison guppies
And when I was done

33:32.469 --> 33:36.349
I'd find a pussy cat and bash in its head.

33:36.515 --> 33:38.438
That's when my momma said

33:38.600 --> 33:40.022
[TIRES SCREECH]

33:40.560 --> 33:42.688
What did she say?

33:43.772 --> 33:46.867
She said
My boy, I think someday.

33:47.025 --> 33:48.493
You'll find a way.

33:48.652 --> 33:51.326
To make your natural tendencies pay.

33:51.488 --> 33:54.788
- You'll be a dentist
CHORUS: You'll be a dentist.

33:54.950 --> 33:57.954
- You have a talent for causing things pain.
- Pain.

33:58.119 --> 34:01.293
- Son, be a dentist.
- Son, be a dentist.

34:01.456 --> 34:04.881
- People will pay you to be inhumane.
- That's inhumane.

34:05.043 --> 34:08.092
<i>Your temperament's wrong
for the priesthood.</i>

34:08.255 --> 34:10.804
- And teaching would suit you still less.
- Aah!

34:10.966 --> 34:13.560
Son, be a dentist.

34:13.717 --> 34:15.719
You'll be a success

34:15.887 --> 34:18.139
[YELLING]

34:25.021 --> 34:27.991
WOMAN:
Here he is folks, the leader of the plaque.

34:28.149 --> 34:29.992
Watch him suck up that gas
Oh, my God

34:30.150 --> 34:31.197
[LAUGHING]

34:31.360 --> 34:34.331
He's a dentist and he'll
never ever be any good.

34:34.489 --> 34:36.708
CHORUS: Who wants their teeth done
By the Marquis de Sade?

34:36.866 --> 34:39.619
Oh, that hurts! Wait, I'm not numb.

34:39.786 --> 34:43.165
Eh, shut up. Open wide, here I come!

34:44.623 --> 34:47.628
- [SINGING] I am your dentist
PATIENT: Goodness gracious.

34:47.793 --> 34:50.797
- And I enjoy the career that I picked.
- You love it

34:50.964 --> 34:54.059
I am your dentist.

34:54.217 --> 34:57.938
- And I get off on the pain I inflict.
- You really love it

34:58.096 --> 35:00.815
I thrill when I drill a bicuspid.

35:00.974 --> 35:05.275
It's swell though they
tell me I'm maladjusted.

35:07.272 --> 35:10.822
- And though it may cause my patients distress.
- No, no, no.

35:10.984 --> 35:13.954
Somewhere
Somewhere in heaven above me

35:14.112 --> 35:17.912
I know
I know that my momma 's proud of me.

35:18.074 --> 35:20.042
Oh, Momma.

35:23.622 --> 35:26.375
[SINGING] 'Cause I'm a dentist.

35:26.541 --> 35:29.135
- And a success.
- Aah!

35:32.005 --> 35:33.427
Say, "Ahh."

35:33.840 --> 35:34.932
[YELLING]

35:35.091 --> 35:36.889
Say, "Ahh."

35:37.052 --> 35:38.269
[GARGLING]

35:38.428 --> 35:39.930
Say, "Ahh!"

35:40.472 --> 35:41.519
[SCREAMING]

35:41.681 --> 35:43.900
Now spit!

35:58.698 --> 36:00.871
[MAN LAUGHING]
[ENGINE ROARING IN DISTANCE]

36:22.055 --> 36:24.808
[INHALES THEN LAUGHS]

36:26.351 --> 36:28.979
Excuse me, sir,
you can't go in there right now.

36:29.145 --> 36:32.069
Relax. You want some nitrous oxide?

36:32.232 --> 36:34.280
- No thanks.
- Suit yourself.

36:35.402 --> 36:37.621
[LAUGHS]

36:37.946 --> 36:39.664
We're closed.

36:41.157 --> 36:42.784
- Well...
- Oh, it's all right, Seymour.

36:42.951 --> 36:44.498
This is my date, my boyfriend.

36:44.661 --> 36:47.460
Seymour, Orin Scrivello.

36:48.206 --> 36:50.925
- D.D.S.
- Hey!

36:51.126 --> 36:53.845
I know you. Sure, I saw you on the news.

36:54.003 --> 36:58.179
I even know your name. Now, let's see.
It's, uh, Cecil. No, no, no.

36:58.341 --> 37:00.764
- It's, uh, Cedric.
- No.

37:00.927 --> 37:02.600
Give me a chance.

37:02.762 --> 37:04.605
It's, uh, ahem...

37:05.056 --> 37:07.479
- Simon?
- Seymour!

37:07.642 --> 37:10.862
- Somebody talking to you?
- Oh, no. Excuse me.

37:11.020 --> 37:12.272
Excuse me, what?

37:12.689 --> 37:15.693
Excuse me, doctor.

37:16.776 --> 37:18.949
That's better.

37:19.279 --> 37:22.453
I know! Sure! You're the plant guy, right?

37:22.615 --> 37:25.960
Well, hey! That means
it must be in there, huh?

37:26.119 --> 37:28.872
Well! That is incredible.

37:29.873 --> 37:32.626
- What do you call that thing?
SEYMOUR: Audrey ll.

37:32.792 --> 37:35.170
Cute name. It's catchy.

37:35.336 --> 37:37.589
Nice plant. Big.

37:37.756 --> 37:40.225
Uh, shouldn't we be leaving now?

37:40.383 --> 37:42.511
You're quite the little chatterbox tonight,
ain't you?

37:42.677 --> 37:44.179
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry, what?

37:44.345 --> 37:47.849
Sorry, doctor. Doctor. Sorry, doctor.

37:48.475 --> 37:50.978
You've got to train them, huh, stud? Heh.

37:51.811 --> 37:52.903
Listen, here's my card.

37:53.062 --> 37:56.157
You ever need a root canal or anything
like that, give me a buzz, you hear?

37:56.316 --> 37:58.944
Now, I'm serious. It's on the house.

37:59.527 --> 38:01.120
Audrey!

38:02.113 --> 38:03.660
You got the handcuffs?

38:03.823 --> 38:06.042
They're right in my bag.

38:07.827 --> 38:10.626
[LAUGHING]

38:36.856 --> 38:39.530
You ought to see the way
he treats her, Twoey.

38:39.692 --> 38:43.617
She deserves a prince,
not a sadistic creep like him.

38:43.863 --> 38:47.163
The man's a total disgrace
to the dental profession.

38:47.575 --> 38:49.748
I don't know what's going on sometimes.

38:49.911 --> 38:52.915
Seems like the whole world's going crazy.

38:53.081 --> 38:55.425
At least we got each other, right?

38:56.209 --> 38:59.554
I'm gonna turn in, Twoey.
I'll see you in the morning.

39:00.338 --> 39:01.840
[THUD]

39:05.260 --> 39:07.388
SEYMOUR:
Oh, boy. Here we go again.

39:07.971 --> 39:10.224
Come on, I haven't got much left.

39:10.390 --> 39:12.267
Just give me a few days to heal, okay?

39:12.433 --> 39:15.357
- Then we'll start again on the
left hand and... TWOEY: Feed me.

39:16.020 --> 39:17.192
I beg your pardon?

39:17.355 --> 39:18.823
Feed me.

39:19.941 --> 39:24.242
Twoey, you talked! You opened your trap,
your thing, and you said...

39:24.404 --> 39:26.623
Feed me, Krelborn! Feed me now!

39:26.781 --> 39:27.828
