01:00:06.853 --> 01:00:10.983
Suddenly Seymour

01:00:11.149 --> 01:00:15.404
ls standing beside me.

01:00:15.570 --> 01:00:19.950
He don't give me orders.

01:00:20.117 --> 01:00:24.497
He don't condescend.

01:00:24.663 --> 01:00:28.588
Suddenly Seymour

01:00:28.750 --> 01:00:33.096
ls here to provide me.

01:00:33.255 --> 01:00:37.726
Sweet understanding.

01:00:37.884 --> 01:00:41.058
- Seymour's my friend.
- Tell me this feeling.

01:00:41.221 --> 01:00:43.098
Lasts 'til forever.

01:00:43.265 --> 01:00:47.270
Tell me the bad times
Are clean washed away.

01:00:47.435 --> 01:00:51.315
Please understand that
It's still strange and frightenin'.

01:00:51.481 --> 01:00:53.529
For losers like I've been.

01:00:53.692 --> 01:00:57.617
It's so hard to say.

01:00:57.779 --> 01:01:01.875
- Suddenly Seymour.
- Suddenly Seymour.

01:01:02.033 --> 01:01:06.129
- He purified me.
- He purified you.

01:01:06.288 --> 01:01:10.543
- Suddenly Seymour.
- Suddenly Seymour.

01:01:10.709 --> 01:01:16.432
- Showed me I can.
- Yes you can.

01:01:16.590 --> 01:01:20.470
Learn how to be more.

01:01:20.635 --> 01:01:24.731
- The girl that's inside me.
- The girl that's inside you.

01:01:24.890 --> 01:01:33.071
- With sweet understanding.
- With sweet understanding.

01:01:33.231 --> 01:01:37.737
With sweet understanding.

01:01:37.903 --> 01:01:39.903
Seymour's your.

01:01:44.367 --> 01:01:45.967
Man

01:02:41.132 --> 01:02:43.476
[CHUCKLING]

01:02:57.565 --> 01:03:00.114
MUSHNIK:
You love her madly, don't you, schmuck?

01:03:00.277 --> 01:03:02.371
Mr. Mushnik, you scared me. I...

01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:06.625
I scared him?
After what I've seen, I scared him?

01:03:06.783 --> 01:03:08.080
[LAUGHS]

01:03:08.243 --> 01:03:11.213
Do you think I didn't know, huh?
Oh, I knew.

01:03:11.371 --> 01:03:14.215
I knew you lay down here
on your pathetic little cot...

01:03:14.374 --> 01:03:15.717
and dreamed about her.

01:03:15.875 --> 01:03:18.094
But I didn't know the lengths
to which you'd go...

01:03:18.253 --> 01:03:20.676
the depths to which you'd sink!

01:03:21.298 --> 01:03:23.300
What depths? What sink?
What are you talking about?

01:03:23.466 --> 01:03:26.094
Little red dots all over the linoleum.

01:03:26.261 --> 01:03:28.980
Little red spots on the concrete outside.

01:03:29.139 --> 01:03:34.521
I'm talking blood, Krelborn.
I'm talking under my own roof.

01:03:35.186 --> 01:03:36.529
An axe murderer!

01:03:36.688 --> 01:03:39.737
TWOEY [SINGING]:
He's got your number now

01:03:39.899 --> 01:03:40.991
I saw everything.

01:03:41.151 --> 01:03:43.574
TWOEY:
He knows just what you've done.

01:03:43.737 --> 01:03:45.410
Everything you did to her boyfriend.

01:03:45.572 --> 01:03:48.325
TWOEY:
You've got no place to hide

01:03:48.491 --> 01:03:49.788
I saw you chopping him.

01:03:49.951 --> 01:03:52.750
TWOEY:
You've got nowhere to run.

01:03:52.912 --> 01:03:55.882
It's true. I chopped him up,
but I didn't kill him!

01:03:56.041 --> 01:03:57.793
TWOEY:
He knows your life of crime.

01:03:57.959 --> 01:03:59.757
Tell it to the police.

01:03:59.919 --> 01:04:03.799
I think it's supper-time.

01:04:03.965 --> 01:04:05.967
Hoo, hoo, whoo.

01:04:06.134 --> 01:04:08.307
Come on, come on.

01:04:08.470 --> 01:04:10.438
Think about all those offers.

01:04:10.597 --> 01:04:13.020
Come on, come on.

01:04:13.183 --> 01:04:14.981
Your future with Audrey.

01:04:15.143 --> 01:04:17.111
Come on, come on.

01:04:17.270 --> 01:04:19.489
<i>Ain't no time to turn squeamish.</i>

01:04:19.647 --> 01:04:21.194
C-C-C-Come on!

01:04:21.358 --> 01:04:23.781
I swear on all my spores.

01:04:23.943 --> 01:04:28.289
When he's gone the world will be yours.

01:04:28.448 --> 01:04:30.746
Yours Yeah, yeah.

01:04:30.909 --> 01:04:34.755
CHORUS [SINGING]:
Come on, come on.

01:04:34.913 --> 01:04:37.513
Come on, come on.

01:04:43.630 --> 01:04:46.230
It's supper-time.

01:04:51.721 --> 01:04:54.975
You know, Krelborn, it kills me doing this.

01:04:55.141 --> 01:05:00.363
But considering you're almost like a son
to me, I'm thinking...

01:05:00.522 --> 01:05:02.445
maybe we don't have to go to the police.

01:05:03.983 --> 01:05:07.032
- We don't?
- I'm thinking...

01:05:07.195 --> 01:05:12.417
what if I kept my mouth shut
and gave you a one-way ticket out of town?

01:05:13.243 --> 01:05:15.211
You'd do that, sir?

01:05:16.329 --> 01:05:20.129
You could lay low for a while,
say 30, 40 years.

01:05:20.291 --> 01:05:23.170
Meanwhile, I would keep the plant.

01:05:24.045 --> 01:05:25.672
- The plant?
MUSHNIK: Of course...

01:05:25.839 --> 01:05:29.184
you'd have to teach me
how to take care of it while you're away.

01:05:29.342 --> 01:05:33.188
Give me your secret gardening tips.

01:05:33.346 --> 01:05:36.646
But then, if you'd rather hang...

01:05:36.808 --> 01:05:40.654
[SINGING] Come on, come on.

01:05:41.438 --> 01:05:48.037
Come on, come on.

01:05:48.194 --> 01:05:50.913
What do I have to do?

01:05:51.072 --> 01:05:53.074
SEYMOUR:
Just feed it.

01:05:53.241 --> 01:05:54.618
Just feed it what?

01:05:54.784 --> 01:05:58.334
[SINGING]
It's supper-time.

01:05:58.913 --> 01:06:00.756
Oh.

01:06:00.915 --> 01:06:03.509
- Minerals.
- Yes.

01:06:04.377 --> 01:06:07.756
Thursdays, you should give it water.

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:09.765
Oh, yes.

01:06:09.924 --> 01:06:11.767
[SINGING] Come on, come on.

01:06:11.926 --> 01:06:13.143
It's supper-time.

01:06:13.678 --> 01:06:16.648
- But whatever you do...
- Yes?

01:06:16.806 --> 01:06:20.777
It's supper-time.

01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:24.360
- Whatever you do...
- Yeah?

01:06:28.860 --> 01:06:30.988
- What the hell is...?
- Sir?

01:06:31.154 --> 01:06:32.906
[TWOEY GROWLS]
[SEYMOUR SHUDDERS]

01:06:33.072 --> 01:06:34.619
MUSHNIK:
Wait! Wait! Wait!

01:06:34.782 --> 01:06:37.376
Aah! Oh, Wait! Aah!

01:06:38.495 --> 01:06:39.542
[SLURPS]

01:06:39.704 --> 01:06:45.256
Supper-time

01:06:48.129 --> 01:06:49.756
Seymour Krelborn!

01:06:49.923 --> 01:06:52.472
Finally, we meet! What an occasion!
Let's toast it. Up yours.

01:06:52.634 --> 01:06:54.432
- Canap?
- Cigarette?

01:06:54.594 --> 01:06:57.768
Let's talk turkey. Sign here.
We'll book you on lecturing tours.

01:06:57.931 --> 01:07:00.400
Yes, darling.
We're sending photographers Thursday.

01:07:00.558 --> 01:07:02.811
So get the plant ready
and wear a clean shirt.

01:07:02.977 --> 01:07:04.570
- Just sign this release.
- Need a pen?

01:07:04.729 --> 01:07:07.198
Aren't you thrilled?
It's the cover of LIFE magazine!

01:07:07.357 --> 01:07:10.236
- Dessert?
- I tell you, son, it's a cinch to get ratings.

01:07:10.401 --> 01:07:12.824
- The title is Marvin's.
- The concept is mine.

01:07:12.987 --> 01:07:15.285
The first weekly gardening show
on a network!

01:07:15.448 --> 01:07:18.167
- And you're gonna host it, you lucky kid.
ALL: Sign!

01:07:18.326 --> 01:07:20.749
CHORUS [SINGING]:
They say the meek shall inherit.

01:07:20.912 --> 01:07:22.960
You know the book doesn't lie.

01:07:23.122 --> 01:07:25.295
It's not a question of merit.

01:07:25.458 --> 01:07:27.677
It's not demand and supply.

01:07:27.835 --> 01:07:30.509
They say the meek gonna get it

01:07:30.672 --> 01:07:32.674
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:07:32.840 --> 01:07:36.344
You know the meek are gonna get
What's comin' to them.

01:07:37.637 --> 01:07:41.107
You know the meek are gonna get
What's comin' to them.

01:07:42.392 --> 01:07:44.486
You know the meek are gonna get
What's comin' to them.

01:07:44.644 --> 01:07:46.644
By and b)'

01:07:53.027 --> 01:07:55.280
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

01:08:00.952 --> 01:08:02.545
Oh, my God!

01:08:03.037 --> 01:08:06.837
And here he is himself,
Mr. Seymour Krelborn!

01:08:07.750 --> 01:08:09.718
Mr. Krelborn, there are
so many questions...

01:08:09.877 --> 01:08:12.426
the American people
in our television audience have for you.

01:08:12.589 --> 01:08:14.842
Come and tell our viewers
at home and elsewhere...

01:08:15.008 --> 01:08:18.353
about this particularly amazing
agricultural phenomenon.

01:08:18.511 --> 01:08:20.354
A phenomenon, I might add,
that has made you...

01:08:20.513 --> 01:08:23.483
one of the most talked-about
plant scientists in the country...

01:08:25.810 --> 01:08:26.857
Cut!

01:08:27.020 --> 01:08:29.863
What the hell? What happened
to the god-damned greenery?

01:08:30.023 --> 01:08:32.651
SEYMOUR: It just needs to be fed.
PRESENTER: So feed it.

01:08:33.151 --> 01:08:34.903
I can't feed it. Not now.

01:08:35.069 --> 01:08:36.912
I'll feed it.
Where do you keep the plant food?

01:08:37.071 --> 01:08:41.076
It doesn't eat plant food.
And I can't feed it now.

01:08:41.242 --> 01:08:44.246
Why don't you leave me alone? All of you.

01:08:44.412 --> 01:08:47.461
Just go away. Leave me alone.
Get out of here.

01:08:47.624 --> 01:08:49.921
Go away. Leave me alone!

01:08:50.084 --> 01:08:51.461
[ALL CHATTERING]

01:08:52.045 --> 01:08:54.468
- Everybody go away! Leave me alone!
- Seymour!

01:08:54.964 --> 01:08:56.591
You're hysterical.

01:08:57.008 --> 01:08:58.180
I know. I'm sorry.

01:08:58.343 --> 01:09:00.470
[ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

01:09:09.895 --> 01:09:12.319
What am I gonna do?
What am I gonna do?

01:09:12.482 --> 01:09:15.736
I never should've started, but I did.
Now, if I don't feed it, it'll die.

01:09:15.902 --> 01:09:17.779
And I'll lose her, I'll lose everything.

01:09:17.944 --> 01:09:21.370
- Seymour? Who are you talking to?
- Oh. Huh?

01:09:21.532 --> 01:09:23.033
Nobody.

01:09:23.201 --> 01:09:25.124
You're acting funny.

01:09:25.286 --> 01:09:27.584
It wasn't nice throwing those people out.

01:09:27.747 --> 01:09:30.500
Those men said
Seymour Krelborn's Gardening Tips...

01:09:30.667 --> 01:09:33.261
is sure to be a very big TV show.

01:09:33.502 --> 01:09:37.006
- I know. I'm sorry. I feel terrible.
- Well, you shouldn't.

01:09:37.173 --> 01:09:40.676
They're coming back tomorrow
and they're bringing you a great big check.

01:09:40.843 --> 01:09:42.345
They are?

01:09:42.511 --> 01:09:45.765
I wish you were enjoying your success.

01:09:46.099 --> 01:09:47.850
They said they're coming back
with money?

01:09:48.017 --> 01:09:49.689
Tomorrow.

01:09:49.852 --> 01:09:51.899
Then we could afford
to get out of here, couldn't we?

01:09:52.063 --> 01:09:53.154
Uh, what do you mean?

01:09:53.314 --> 01:09:55.863
That's it. After tomorrow
we could leave here together.

01:09:56.401 --> 01:09:57.823
Together?

01:09:58.945 --> 01:10:00.538
If you'll have me.

01:10:00.697 --> 01:10:02.290
Audrey, will you have me?

01:10:02.907 --> 01:10:04.375
Uh, what do you mean?

01:10:04.992 --> 01:10:06.835
Marry me, Audrey.

01:10:06.994 --> 01:10:09.918
- Oh, Seymour, this is so sudden.
- Will you?

01:10:16.129 --> 01:10:17.802
Sure.

01:10:18.297 --> 01:10:20.516
Then that's it!
We'll go get married right now.

01:10:20.675 --> 01:10:22.848
- Oh, Seymour!
- Tomorrow we'll come back...

01:10:23.010 --> 01:10:26.014
I'll be on television, get the money
and then we'll live happy ever after.

01:10:26.180 --> 01:10:29.309
Oh, Audrey, I'll give you a wonderful life
with no plants, I promise.

01:10:29.475 --> 01:10:32.069
- No plants at all.
- You're talking peculiar again, Seymour.

01:10:32.228 --> 01:10:34.526
We'll start tonight,
we'll go to City Hall, get married...

01:10:34.689 --> 01:10:37.442
and then spend the night somewhere
it's safe. Some nice hotel.

01:10:37.608 --> 01:10:39.906
- Oh, Seymour.
- Oh, Audrey.

01:10:40.069 --> 01:10:41.867
Oh, I've got to get ready! Heh!

01:10:42.029 --> 01:10:44.202
Hurry. Hurry.

01:11:48.679 --> 01:11:51.649
Feed me.

01:11:51.808 --> 01:11:55.358
- Under no circumstances.
- Feed me.

01:11:55.520 --> 01:11:57.693
I will not, so stop asking.

01:11:57.855 --> 01:11:59.232
Feed me!

01:11:59.398 --> 01:12:02.447
No! No more!
I can't take living with the guilt.

01:12:03.069 --> 01:12:04.616
Tough titty.

01:12:04.987 --> 01:12:08.537
- Watch your language.
- Aw, out the crap. Bring on the meat.

01:12:09.367 --> 01:12:11.244
Okay, okay.

01:12:11.577 --> 01:12:14.751
I'll bring you meat. I'll run down to the
corner, pick you up some ground round.

01:12:14.914 --> 01:12:18.839
- How about that?
- Don't do me no favours!

01:12:19.001 --> 01:12:20.719
- Look.
- Hmm?

01:12:20.878 --> 01:12:23.757
It's my last offer. Yes or no?

01:12:23.923 --> 01:12:28.554
You sure do drive a hard bargain.

01:12:29.554 --> 01:12:32.148
Done. Fine. Great.

01:12:34.308 --> 01:12:36.606
Don't think you're getting dessert.

01:12:41.148 --> 01:12:43.150
[CHUCKLES]

01:12:55.288 --> 01:12:56.335
Unh.

01:13:03.337 --> 01:13:06.386
[GRUNTING]

01:13:12.638 --> 01:13:14.640
[GROANS]

01:13:33.910 --> 01:13:35.958
[CHUCKLES]

01:13:52.929 --> 01:13:54.306
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:13:59.810 --> 01:14:01.483
[HUMMING]

01:14:05.316 --> 01:14:07.489
[HUMMING]

01:14:08.361 --> 01:14:10.363
[PHONE RINGS]

01:14:13.282 --> 01:14:14.329
Hello.

01:14:14.492 --> 01:14:16.460
TWOEY [SINGING]:
Hey, little lady, hello.

01:14:16.619 --> 01:14:18.496
Who...? Who is this?

01:14:18.663 --> 01:14:21.507
You're looking cute as can be.

01:14:21.666 --> 01:14:23.168
Is this someone I know?

01:14:23.334 --> 01:14:26.213
You're looking mighty sweet

01:14:27.088 --> 01:14:28.340
Seymour!

01:14:28.506 --> 01:14:32.010
No, it ain't Seymour. Ha, ha, it's me!

01:14:34.095 --> 01:14:35.597
[LAUGHING]

01:14:35.763 --> 01:14:38.687
AUDREY:
Oh, my God!

01:14:50.945 --> 01:14:52.538
[CAR HORN HONKING]

01:14:56.993 --> 01:14:59.246
I don't believe it.

01:14:59.412 --> 01:15:02.040
Believe it, baby. It talks.

01:15:02.623 --> 01:15:04.091
Am I dreaming this?

01:15:04.250 --> 01:15:07.094
No, and you ain't in Kansas, neither.

01:15:09.463 --> 01:15:11.511
Something is very wrong here.

01:15:11.674 --> 01:15:14.928
I need me some water in the worst way.

01:15:15.094 --> 01:15:16.971
Look at my branches.

01:15:17.138 --> 01:15:20.017
I'm drying up. I'm a goner, honey!

01:15:20.182 --> 01:15:21.229
[LAUGHS]

01:15:21.392 --> 01:15:23.815
[SINGING]
Come on and give me a drink

01:15:23.978 --> 01:15:25.651
I don't know if I should.

01:15:25.813 --> 01:15:28.191
Hey, little lady, be nice.

01:15:28.357 --> 01:15:29.859
Do you talk to Seymour like this?

01:15:30.026 --> 01:15:32.905
Sure do I'll drink it straight.

01:15:33.070 --> 01:15:34.538
Your leaves are dry, poor thing.

01:15:34.697 --> 01:15:37.166
Don '2' need no glass or no ice.

01:15:37.324 --> 01:15:38.871
Uh, I'll get the can.

01:15:39.035 --> 01:15:42.084
Don '2' need no twist of lime.

01:15:42.246 --> 01:15:43.338
Here we go.

01:15:43.497 --> 01:15:45.841
And now it's supper-time!

01:15:47.501 --> 01:15:48.923
Oh!

01:15:49.086 --> 01:15:51.339
Ah, ha-ha-ha.

01:15:52.256 --> 01:15:54.975
Oh, relax, doll,
and it'll be easier.

01:15:55.134 --> 01:15:59.105
Come join your dentist friend and Mushnik,
ha, ha.

01:15:59.263 --> 01:16:04.770
- Aah!
- They're right inside. Ha-ha-ha!

01:16:04.977 --> 01:16:06.775
[GASPING]

01:16:06.937 --> 01:16:09.861
[TWOEY LAUGHING]

01:16:10.149 --> 01:16:12.072
[SCREAMING]

01:16:12.651 --> 01:16:14.153
[CRUNCH]

01:16:17.490 --> 01:16:20.585
SEYMOUR:
Get off of her! Get off!

01:16:21.660 --> 01:16:22.786
[AUDREY SCREAMING]

01:16:34.548 --> 01:16:37.017
[LAUGHING]

01:16:47.561 --> 01:16:50.405
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

01:16:50.564 --> 01:16:52.407
No.

01:16:57.071 --> 01:16:59.039
Don't die, Audrey. Please don't die.

01:17:00.616 --> 01:17:05.622
You know, the plant just said
the strangest thing just now.

01:17:05.788 --> 01:17:08.462
It said Orin and Mr. Mushnik...

01:17:08.624 --> 01:17:10.797
are already inside.

01:17:12.670 --> 01:17:14.297
It's true.

01:17:14.463 --> 01:17:16.261
I did it.

01:17:16.674 --> 01:17:18.893
I fed them to it.

01:17:19.760 --> 01:17:24.061
And that's what made it
so big and strong...

01:17:24.807 --> 01:17:27.811
and you so famous?

01:17:27.977 --> 01:17:30.275
I've done terrible things, Audrey.

01:17:30.437 --> 01:17:34.738
- But not to you. Never to you.
- But...

01:17:37.653 --> 01:17:40.532
I want you to, Seymour.

01:17:41.031 --> 01:17:42.658
What?

01:17:43.993 --> 01:17:48.749
When I die, which should be very shortly...

01:17:49.039 --> 01:17:51.167
give me to the plant.

01:17:51.333 --> 01:17:57.090
So that it will live, and bring you
all the wonderful things you deserve.

01:17:57.256 --> 01:18:01.056
- You don't know what you're saying.
- But I do.

01:18:01.218 --> 01:18:04.973
It's the one gift I can give you.

01:18:05.139 --> 01:18:07.483
And if I'm in the plant...

01:18:07.641 --> 01:18:10.861
then I am part of the plant.

01:18:11.770 --> 01:18:13.864
So in a way...

01:18:15.691 --> 01:18:18.615
we'll always be together.

01:18:20.863 --> 01:18:26.461
[SINGING]
You'll wash my tender leaves.

01:18:26.660 --> 01:18:32.713
You'll smell my sweet perfume.

01:18:33.125 --> 01:18:37.551
You'll water me and care for me.

01:18:37.755 --> 01:18:42.556
You'll see me bud and bloom

01:18:42.760 --> 01:18:47.516
I'm feeling strangely happy now.

01:18:47.723 --> 01:18:54.732
Contented and serene.

01:18:55.564 --> 01:19:01.446
Oh, don't you see.

01:19:02.196 --> 01:19:07.828
Finally I'll be.

01:19:09.995 --> 01:19:14.091
Somewhere.

01:19:14.792 --> 01:19:17.796
That's.

01:19:20.130 --> 01:19:21.730
Green

